  "prompt": "Is it okay to donate books to a toy drive?",
  "response": "It generally depends on the specific guidelines of the toy drive. Many toy drives prioritize toys and other items specifically meant for children, but some may accept books as well, especially if they are intended for children or families in need. To be sure, it's best to check the donation guidelines of the toy drive you're considering. If they accept books, make sure they are in good condition and appropriate for the age group they serve. If they don't accept books, consider donating them to a library, school, or organization that does accept books for children.",
